gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 137, Pacers 126
gameRecap.excerpt: Led by Tyrese Maxeys career-high 50 points, the 76ers defeated Pacers, 137-126. Maxey added seven rebounds, five assists and three blocks, while Joel Embiid notched 37 points, 13 rebounds and seven assists for the 76ers in the victory. Tyrese Haliburton tallied 25 points and 17 assists for the Pacers in the losing effort. The 76ers have won eight consecutive games as they improve to 8-1 on the season, while the Pacers fall to 6-4.
